The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has announced 240 fresh cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) in 13 States and the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja. The new figure brings the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 155,657. The health agency made the announcement yesterday night while giving the daily report on its official website. According to the report, about five persons died in the last 24 hours due to the COVID-19 complications. The report reads: “240 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Anambra-85
Lagos-82
Osun-17
Ogun-10
Kwara-9
FCT-8
Kano-7
Abia-6
Borno-4
Edo-2
Bayelsa-2
Kaduna-2
Rivers-1 155,657 confirmed
133,768 discharged
1,907 deaths “Our discharges today includes 170 community recoveries in Lagos State managed in line with guidelines”.